Donald J. DOCKERY, Appellant, v. Timothy P. BURNS; Scott C. Sladek; John J. Jedlicka; William H. Ouren; Omaha Public Defender’s Office, Appellees. No. 07-1228. United States Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. Submitted: Oct. 23, 2007. Filed: Nov. 7, 2007. Donald J. Dockery, Omaha, NE, pro se.

Before MURPHY, SMITH, and SHEPHERD, Circuit Judges.

[UNPUBLISHED]

PER CURIAM.

Donald Dockery appeals the district court’s1 preservice dismissal of his 42 U.S.C. § 1983 complaint for failure to state a claim. Upon de novo review, see Moore v. Sims, 200 F.3d 1170, 1171 (8th Cir.2000) (per curiam), we conclude that dismissal was proper. Accordingly, we affirm the judgment of the district court. See 8th Cir. R. 47B.

. The Honorable Richard G. Kopf, United States District Judge for the District of Nebraslca.
